dc_title_s: Braunswyck et Meydburg cum terris adjacentibus; sculpersunt E. S. Hamersveldt et S. Rogeri.
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Illustrations around the title cartouche depict a woman holding wheat and fruit and a cherub pouring wine into a glass held by a man. From "Atlantis maioris appendix", Johannes Janssonius, 1630. 1 map; 37 x 47 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
dc_creator_sm: Jansson, Jan, 1588-1664.,Jansson, Jan, 1588-1664. Atlantes Maioris Appendix, 1630.,Vignaud, Henry, 1830-1922, former owner.
